===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[quotation]] [[mark]]}} ''(normally plural)''

# {{UK}} One of a pair of [[quotation marks]] used to denote a [[quotation]] in writing. The mark at the beginning ''(opening quotation mark)'' is <big>'''[[“]]'''</big>  or <big>'''[[‘]]'''</big>, and the mark at the end ''(closing quotation mark) is <big>'''[[”]]'''</big> or <big>'''[[’]]'''</big>.
# {{North America}} One of a pair of [[quotation marks]] used to denote a quotation in writing. The same [[symbol]] is used at both the beginning and the end of the quotation, which is usually the  "[[double quote]]" symbol <big>'''[["]]'''</big>, although the "[[single quote]]" symbol <big>'''[[']] '''</big> is sometimes used, especially to denote a quotation within a quotation.

